title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1993-06-21
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Spoonful, Jack A Roe, Black Throated Wind, Loose Lucy, Eternity, So Many Roads, Promised Land

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Women Are Smarter-> Ship of Fools, Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Black Peter-> Around & Around, E: I Fought The Law

reviews.review_text:
What a show!  Darn good recording. The band was red hot and ready for this show, or the energy of the crowd was a powerful stimulant, or both.

From the first song Jerry is on fire.  This is from that streak in '93 where Jerry seemed to be making a comeback, really firing "on all cylinders", seemed to feel good - had the words down, and the guitar - oh man, the guitar!!

As I look for "gems" in the last years after Brent's death, this one is one of the most beautiful.

The recording is outside, and at first seems disappointing - but everything is there, and the spread is wide and complete - and balanced.  After a few minutes one realises this is a pretty darn true reproduction of this outside show, and one wonderful concert.

How bout that Spoonful???
